<!doctype HTML>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>30 Day Challenge - information</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="stylesheets/style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>About 30 Day Challenge at CLS</h1>
      <p>30 Day Challenge at CLS will run from the 25th of November to the 20th of December.</p>
      <p>Each challenge is available between 07:00 and 18:00.</p>
      <p>Have fun!</p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>lars.j.andersson@chalmers.se<br/>sofia.toivonen@chalmers.se</p>
      <h2>Your data</h2>
      <p>By accepting and signing in to 30 Day Challenge we will get access to your email.</p>
      <p>We will store data about your progress in 30 Day Challenge on our server which is located in Northern Europe.</p>
      <p>The data will be deleted if you have been inactive for more than three months.</p>
      <p>Anonymized data will be saved so that we can evaluate the usage of 30 Day Challenge.</p>
      <p>We will also store data and a cookie on your machine to be able to see that you have logged in and that you have accepted our data handling.</p>
      <p>Contact us if you want to have your data removed.</p>
      <button id="login-button" type=button>Accept and continue to 30 Day Challenge</button>
    </main>
    <script>
      let dataPlanAcceptedServer = <%= dataPlanAccepted %>;

      let dataPlanAccepted = dataPlanAcceptedServer;

      if (dataPlanAccepted) {
        document.getElementById("login-button").innerHTML = "Go to 30 Day Challenge";
      }

      document.getElementById("login-button").addEventListener("click", function() {
        localStorage.setItem("30dc-cls-data-accept", 1);
        window.location.href="/login";
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>